entry.content: Replying to @Trista French 1. It has to have dill (herb or flavor) to be labeled “dill” on the front of the package. 2. A container of pickles does not have to contain dill to be labeled as “pickles” on the front of the package. 3. Dill may be listed as “spice” or “natural flavor” in the ingredient declaration, so even if dill is added, it may not be listed as “dill” on the ingredient declaration. 4. Yes, I said pickles a lot in this video 🙃 #picklegate #pickle #pickles #foodlabels #foodscience #greenscreen
